  "market_context": "NQ daily chart showing bullish order flow with consecutive closes over previous day highs. A prior wick's consequent encroachment was violated and price continued upward each day, making previous day high the natural draw on liquidity for the next session.",
  "key_observation": "London failed to put in a low, instead sweeping one side of the range and forming a failure swing with equal highs at previous day high. The 8:30 New York manipulation then swept external liquidity opposite to order flow, setting up a long continuation matching the 4H Power of 3.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily chart, identify bullish order flow — wick's consequent encroachment violated and each day closing over previous day high, making PDH the target.",
    "Step 2: Drop to the 15-minute chart to frame a long entry; observe London does not form a tradable low but instead takes one side of the range and moves back inside, leaving equal highs with PDH as a failure swing.",
    "Step 3: As New York approaches, note the sweep of external liquidity opposite to order flow (manipulation phase).",
    "Step 4: Drop to the 5-minute chart and locate the change in state of delivery — a close above the series of down-close candles, paired with a fair value gap.",
    "Step 5: Take dual entries: one on the order block and one on the fair value gap, both targeting previous day high.",
    "Step 6: Confirm context — the 4-hour candle represents accumulation, manipulation, and distribution (Power of 3) targeting PDH.",
    "Step 7: Add confluences using standard deviation projections — the -2 to -2.5 level aligns with PDH and -4 to -4.5 aligns with max expansion."
  ],
  "outcome": "Both entries (OB and FVG) tagged in; price moved higher and hit take profit at previous day high.",
  "lessons": "When daily order flow is clearly bullish and London fails to form a low, wait for the New York 8:30 sweep of external liquidity opposite to order flow. A 5-min CISD paired with a fair value gap allows dual entries (OB or FVG) targeting previous day high.",
